noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 provides the values of 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{t_{i}p_{j}|t_{m}p_{n}\times t_{k}p_{\ell}}$
\end_inset

 for the different receiver and donor genotypes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

\series bold
Costs of choice and ornamentation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
We assume that costs of choice and ornamentation affect fecundity 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 of genotype 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}p_{j}$
\end_inset

 (susceptible) or 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}p_{j}\times t_{k}p_{\ell}$
\end_inset

 (infected), where fecundity is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
b_{t_{i}p_{j}} & =\exp\left[-c_{t}\delta_{t_{2}}-c_{p}\delta_{p_{2}}\right]\label{eq:btipj}
\end{align}

\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{t}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{p}$
\end_inset

 are scalars reflecting how rapidly birth rates reduce by bearing ornamentation
 or expressing preferences, while 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{t_{2}}$
\end_inset

 (or 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{p_{2}}$
\end_inset

) is Kronecker's delta which has value 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 in case the cell contains allele 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{2}$
\end_inset

 (or 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{2}$
\end_inset

) and is 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 otherwise.
 For infected plasmids with genotype 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}p_{j}\times t_{k}p_{\ell}$
\end_inset

, the values of 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{t_{2}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{p_{2}}$
\end_inset

 are
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\delta_{t_{2}} & =\begin{cases}
0 & t_{i}=t_{k}=t_{1}\\
h_{t} & t_{i}=t_{1},t_{k}=t_{2};t_{i}=t_{1},t_{k}=t_{2}\\
1 & t_{i}=t_{k}=t_{2}
\end{cases}\\
\delta_{p_{2}} & =\begin{cases}
0 & p_{i}=p_{k}=p_{1}\\
h_{p} & p_{i}=t_{1},t_{k}=t_{2};t_{i}=t_{1},t_{k}=t_{2}\\
1 & t_{i}=t_{k}=t_{2}
\end{cases},
\end{align*}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{t}$
\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{p}$
\end_inset

 reflect the 
